    <h1>Installation Prerequisites</h1>
    <h2>Introduction</h2>
    <p>eSciDoc is a complex software stack, consisting of various software components. This installer will guide you
      step by step through the installation process. However, it may be necessary to install and configure a runtime 
      environment prior to running this installer. The runtime environment consists of two components:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Java JDK</li>
      <li>Relational Database</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Please make sure both software components are properly installed onto the machine you will install the 
      eSciDoc Infrastructure.
    </p>
    <h2>Java JDK</h2>
    <p>Running the eSciDoc Infrastructure requires a Java Software Development Kit (JDK). A run-time environment (JRE)
      is sufficient to run this installer, but starting the system after a successful installation will fail. Please make
      sure that you have a JDK Version 1.6 or newer installed on your system.
    </p>
    <p>You can download the latest JDK software at no cost from 
    <a href="http://java.sun.com/javase/downloads/">http://java.sun.com/javase/downloads/</a>.</p>
    <h2>Relational Database Management System</h2>
    <p>The eSciDoc Infrastructure currently supports Oracle as commercial and PostgreSQL as open source database management system.</p> 
    <ul>
      <li>Oracle 10g or newer</li>
      <li>PostgreSQL 8.4 or newer</li>
      <!--li>MySQL 5.0 or newer</li-->
    </ul>
    <p>The database needs to be up and running during the installation process. You will need to provide credentials 
      for a database user with sufficient privileges to create login roles and databases. This user will only be used
      to create two login roles (typically "fedoraAdmin" and "escidoc") and three databases ("fedora3", "escidoc-core", 
      "riTriples").  
    </p>  
    <p>
      If you want to use an existing instance of PostgreSQL (which may reside on a remote server), 
      please make sure that it meets the following requirements:
    </p>
    <h3>PostgreSQL</h3>
    <table>
      <tr><td>Software version:</td><td>&ge; 8.4</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Database encoding:</td><td>UTF-8</td></tr>
    </table>  
